Do you set this environmental variable?

```
GS_LIB=${GMTHOME}/share/ghostscript/9.53.3/Resource/Init
```

This can fix the bug.

without the environmental variable:
````bash
$ which gs
/Applications/GMT-6.2.0.app/Contents/Resources/bin/gs
````
So, I thought the gs is fine because the gs is installed with gmt6.2.0.
When using the macOS bundle, you need to follow the instructions at the end of the GMT splash screen.
